<subSubSection id="75EA655CFFA7FFCAFF309BFEFE0ADEE3" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3D4F36D7FFA7FFCAFF309BFEFA54DDF8" blockId="65.[151,1436,1249,1703]" box="[151,1436,1445,1469]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="0F84EAC5FFA7FFCAFF309BFEFEC3DDF8" bold="true" box="[151,267,1445,1469]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The status of the species of 
<taxonomicName id="FAF04D54FFA7FFCAFDC99BFEFD02DDF8" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" box="[622,714,1445,1469]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Libystes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0F84EAC5FFA7FFCAFDC99BFEFD02DDF8" box="[622,714,1445,1469]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Libystes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in need of revision (
<bibRefCitation id="59614B26FFA7FFCAFC4D9BFEFADCDDF8" author="Apel &amp; Spiridonov" box="[1002,1300,1445,1469]" firstAuthor="Apel" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="159 - 331" refId="ref91443" refString="Apel, M. &amp; Spiridonov, V. A. (1998) Taxonomy and zoogeography of the portunid crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Brachyura: Portunidae) of the Arabian Gulf and adjacent waters. Fauna of Arabia, 17, 159 - 331." type="journal article" year="1998">Apel &amp; Spiridonov 1998</bibRefCitation>
; Ng 2011).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D4F36D7FFA7FFCAFF309B97FA54DDA1" blockId="65.[151,1436,1249,1703]" box="[151,1436,1484,1508]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Although some (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="59614B26FFA7FFCAFE2C9B97FD74DDA1" author="Vannini &amp; Innocenti" box="[395,700,1484,1508]" firstAuthor="Vannini" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="252 - 298" refId="ref119212" refString="Vannini, M. &amp; Innocenti, G. (2000) Portunidae (Crustacea Brachyura). Research on the coast of Somalia. Tropical Zoology, 13, 252 - 298." type="journal article" year="2000">Vannini &amp; Innocenti 2000</bibRefCitation>
) regard 
<taxonomicName id="FAF04D54FFA7FFCAFCB99B96FC5CDDA1" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1924" box="[798,916,1484,1508]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Libystes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="0F84EAC5FFA7FFCAFCB99B96FC5CDDA1" box="[798,916,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">L. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="FAF04D54FFA7FFCAFB139B96FAE9DDA1" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" box="[1204,1313,1484,1508]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Libystes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidus">
<emphasis id="0F84EAC5FFA7FFCAFB139B96FAE9DDA1" box="[1204,1313,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">L. nitidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A. Milne-
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D4F36D7FFA7FFCAFF309BA8FD30DE74" blockId="65.[151,1436,1249,1703]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Edwards, 1867, it is a valid species (Ng 2011). The Hawaiian specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="FAF04D54FFA7FFCAFC519BAFFBA1DE4E" authorityName="Rathbun" authorityYear="1924" box="[1014,1129,1523,1547]" class="Malacostraca" family="Portunidae" genus="Libystes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis id="0F84EAC5FFA7FFCAFC519BAFFBA1DE4E" box="[1014,1129,1523,1547]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">L. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, may represent a distinct species (P.K.L. Ng, personal communication).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D4F36D7FFA7FFCAFF30981AFE50DE1D" blockId="65.[151,1436,1249,1703]" box="[151,408,1600,1625]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="0F84EAC5FFA7FFCAFF30981AFED5DE1C" bold="true" box="[151,285,1601,1625]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" reason="1">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
Ng (2011)
</paragraph>
